Note: it replace the old emacs automaticlly. emacs or Emacs both work.
emacs --version.
allude to :'http://wikemacs.org/wiki/Installing_Emacs_on_OS_X'
2. Install org-mode:

I use the git depository.
$ cd ~/path/you/store/package
$ git clone https://code.orgmode.org/bzg/org-mode.git
$ cd org-mode/
$ make autoloads
Allude to :https://orgmode.org/manual/Installation.html

## the problem I met when make autoloads
Loading /Users/zigongxu/git/emacs-package/org-mode/lisp/org-compat.el (source)...Cannot open load file: cl-lib

That is because the emacs version is out of date and I only update as above then it work. The path that installation suggest to change 
probabaly no need to change. Moreover, that command cause a error after start new Emacs.


